{{Infobox film festival | name = Chale Wote Street Art Festival | logo = | image = Kid Art.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = Kid art at 2013 Chale Wote | number = | location = [[Accra]], Ghana | language = International | website = [http://accradotalttours.wordpress.com/category/chale-wote-street-art-festival/ Accra Dot Alt Chale Wote Pages] }}
The '''Chale Wote Street Art Festival''' <ref>{{cite web|title=Four Word Story: Chale Wote Street Art Festival|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=238025|publisher=Ghana Web|accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Chale Wote Street festival brings street art to James Town|url=http://www.ghanamusic.com/news/upcoming-events/chale-wote-street-festival-brings-street-art-to-james-town/index.html|publisher=Ghanamusic.com|accessdate=8 September 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120212932/http://www.ghanamusic.com/news/upcoming-events/chale-wote-street-festival-brings-street-art-to-james-town/index.html|archivedate=20 November 2012|df=}}</ref> also known as '''Chale Wote''' is an alternative platform that brings [[art]], [[music]], [[dance]] and performance out into the [[Street|streets]]. The [[festival]] targets exchanges between scores of local and [[international]] artists and patrons by creating and appreciating art together.
Since 2011, CHALE WOTE has included street painting, graffiti murals, photography, theater, spoken word, interactive art installations, live street performances, extreme sports, film shows, a fashion parade, a music block party, recyclable design workshops and much more. It is the first to be organized<ref name="CW2011" /> in [[Accra]], [[Ghana]] and has inspired similar events across the country. There have been 6 editions so far; the first two ran for one day each, while the 2013 and 2014 edition ran concurrently for two days, the former in September and the latter in August, a week after the Homowo festival of the Ga people at the historical [[Jamestown, Ghana]] on the [[High Street]] in Accra. The format switched in 2016 when the festival lasted an entire week, from August 18 - 21. This switch saw the festival hop from the open street gallery that is Jamestown to other art spaces, such as the [[Nubuke Foundation]], the Museum of Science and Technology as well as film screenings at the Movenpick Ambassador Hotel. The same format will be replicated in the 7th edition, themed, Wata Mata <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://accradotaltradio.com/2017/04/chale-wote-2017-call-artists/|title=CHALE WOTE 2017: CALL FOR ARTISTS|last=|first=|date=4 April 2017|website=ACCRA[dot]ALT|accessdate=4 August 2017}}</ref>with further immersion into Accra, spreading to areas such as Nima, Osu and more. The event is produced by Accra [dot] Alt Radio,<ref>{{cite web|title=ACCRA [dot] ALT Radio {{!}} Live from the Ghana Space Station|url=http://www.accradotaltradio.com/|publisher=Accra [dot] Alt Radio|accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref> with support from other local cultural networks like Attukwei Art Foundation, Foundation for Contemporary Art Ghana, Dr. Monk, Redd Kat Pictures and the [[Institut français]] in Ghana.{{Citation needed|date=April 2014}}
