'''Hi-wa itck''' is a tradition concerning [[lovesickness]] mostly associated with the [[Mohave people|Mohave American Indians]]. This syndrome is associated with the separation of a loved one and the symptoms include [[insomnia]], [[Depression (clinical)|depression]] and [[loss of appetite]] and possibly [[suicide]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Glossary of culture bound syndromes |url=http://www.mccajor.net/cbs_glos.html }}</ref> Hi-wa itck was typically experienced by men, especially older men abandoned by their younger wives.<ref>Devereux 95, 103</ref>
