{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox government agency | name = Ministry of Religious Affairs and Culture (Myanmar) | native_name = | native_name_a = {{my|သာသနာရေးနှင့်ယဉ်ကျေးမှုဝန်ကြီးဌာန}} | native_name_r = | type = Ministry | seal = File:Seal of MORC Myanmar.jpg | seal_width = | seal_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | formed = {{start date and age|1 April 2016}} | preceding1 = Ministry of Religious Affairs | preceding2 = Ministry of Culture<!-- up to |preceding6= --> | dissolved = | superseding1 = | superseding2 = <!-- up to |superseding6= --> | jurisdiction = {{flaglist|Myanmar}} | headquarters = [[Nay Pyi Taw]] | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LATITUDE|LONGITUDE|type:landmark_region:US|display=inline,title}} --> | motto = | employees = | budget = | minister1_name = [[Aung Ko (politician)|Aung Ko]] (Thura)
| minister1_pfo = | minister2_name = | minister2_pfo = <!-- up to |minister8_name= --> | deputyminister1_name = | deputyminister1_pfo = | deputyminister2_name = | deputyminister2_pfo = <!-- up to |deputyminister8_name= --> | deputy = | child1_agency = | child2_agency = <!-- up to |child25_agency= --> | keydocument1 = <!-- up to |keydocument6= --> | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | agency_id = | map = | map_size = | map_caption = | footnotes = | embed = }}
The '''Ministry of Religious Affairs and Culture''' ({{Lang-my|သာသနာရေးနှင့်ယဉ်ကျေးမှုဝန်ကြီးဌာန}}, abbreviated '''MORAC''') administers the religious affairs, cultural affairs and historical and archaeology research efforts of [[Myanmar]] (formerly Burma). The Department of Religious Affairs purification, perpetuation, promotion and propagation of the [[Theravada]] Buddhist Sasana and promotes Myanmar traditional customs and culture.<ref name="Self3">{{cite web|url=http://www.mora.gov.mm/mora_ministry1.aspx|title=The Ministry of Religious Affairs|publisher=Ministry Of Religious Affairs|accessdate=19 February 2012}}</ref>
==History==
The Ministry of Culture was established on 16 March 1952 as the Ministry of Union Cultures, and later renamed the Ministry of Culture on 15 March 1972.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.modins.net/myanmarinfo/ministry/culture.htm|title=Ministry Of Culture|date=2002|work=Myanmar Online Data Information Network Solutions|accessdate=27 June 2015}}</ref>
The Ministry of Religious Affairs (MORA) came into being before the [[Union of Myanmar]] regained its Independence in 1947. On 2 March 1962, the [[Union Revolutionary Council|Revolutionary Council]] government reorganised all ministries. The Ministry of Religious Affairs became a department of the Ministry of Home and Religious Affairs. On 18 September 1988. the [[State Law and Order Restoration Council]] (SLORC) formed the Department for the Promotion and Propagation of the Sasana, also under the Ministry of Home and Religious Affairs. On 20 March 1992. the ministries of Home Affairs and Religious Affairs were separated. A cabinet meeting on 26 June 1998 confirmed that the [[International Theravada Buddhist Missionary University]] would be formed under MORA.<ref name="Self2">{{cite web|url=http://www.mora.gov.mm/mora_ministry1.aspx|title=The Ministry of Religious Affairs|publisher=Ministry Of Religious Affairs|accessdate=19 February 2012}}</ref> MORA's motto was a [[Pali]] phrase "''Buddha sāsanaṃ ciraṃ tiṭṭhatu''" ({{my|ဗုဒ္ဓသာသနံစိရံတိဋ္ဌတု}}), which translates as "Long Live the Buddhist Sasana."
On 1 April 2016, the Ministry of Religious Affairs and Ministry of Culture were combined to form the Ministry of Religious Affairs and Culture, as part of a government downsizing.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mmtimes.com/national-news/nay-pyi-taw/19532-nld-reduces-government-ministries.html|title=NLD reduces government ministries|work=The Myanmar Times|access-date=2018-10-02|language=en}}</ref>
==Departments== *Union Minister Office *Department of Religious Affairs ** To ensure that all people living in the Union of Myanmar can freely believe in any religion and freely practice that religion. ** Since the great majority of the people are Buddhist, to purify, perpetuate and propagate the three kinds of Sasana of the Buddha namely, Pariyatti, Patipatti and Pativedha. ** To preserve and promote the traditional and cultural heritage of Myanmar.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mora.gov.mm/mora_department1.aspx|title=Department of Religious Affairs|publisher=Ministry of Religious Affairs|accessdate=19 February 2012}}</ref> *Department for Promotion and Propagation of Sasana - Responsible for supporting missionary activity within Myanmar and abroad. It also undertakes translation of [[Pitakas]] and compilation of Buddhist Treatises **[[State Pariyatti Sasana University, Yangon]] **[[State Pariyatti Sasana University, Mandalay]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mora.gov.mm/mora_sasana1.aspx|title=Department for the Promotion and Propagation of Sasana|publisher=Ministry of Religious Affairs|accessdate=19 February 2012}}</ref> *[[International Theravada Buddhist Missionary University]] *Department of Archaeology and [[National Museum of Myanmar|National Museum]] *Fine Arts Department *Department of Historical Research and [[National Library of Myanmar|National Library]] *[[National University of Arts and Culture, Yangon]] *[[National University of Arts and Culture, Mandalay]]
